PIXE measurements were taken using a National Electrostatics Corporation 1.7 MeV tandem Pelletron particle accelerator at the Hope College Ion Beam Analysis Laboratory (HIBAL). X-ray emission, measured with a XR-100SDD Silicon Drift Detector (Amptek Inc., Bedford, MA, USA) was induced by a beam of 3.4 MeV protons with a beam current of ∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
